   "source": [
    "# 📓 Training: Building Knowledge Bases for NotebookLM-style Apps\n",
    "**Objective:** Learn how to prepare real-world data, clean it, and structure it so that an AI (like NotebookLM) can provide accurate, grounded answers using a technique called **RAG (Retrieval Augmented Generation)**.\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 🛠️ Module 1: The Concept of \"Grounding\"\n",
    "In standard AI, the model guesses based on general training data. In a \"NotebookLM\" style program, the AI is **grounded** in your specific documents.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Real-Life Example:** \n",
    "Imagine you are a doctor. Instead of asking a general AI \"How to treat a patient?\", you give the AI *this specific patient's medical history* and ask, \"Based on this history, what is the risk of this specific medication?\""
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 📦 Module 2: Preparing the Data (The \"Source\")\n",
    "AI models have a \"context window\" (a limit on how much they can read at once). We must break long documents into smaller, meaningful \"chunks.\"\n",
    "\n",
    "**Real-Life Example:** A Company Employee Handbook."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Install necessary libraries\n",
    "!pip install nltk\n",
    "\n",
    "import re\n",
    "import nltk\n",
    "from nltk.tokenize import sent_tokenize\n",
    "nltk.download('punkt')\n",
    "nltk.download('punkt_tab')\n",
    "\n",
    "# REAL LIFE EXAMPLE: A messy company policy document\n",
    "raw_document = \"\"\"\n",
    "Welcome to TechCorp! 🚀 \n",
    "Our vacation policy is simple: Employees get 20 days of PTO per year. \n",
    "Wait, actually, for senior staff, it's 25 days. Please contact HR at hr@techcorp.com.\n",
    "---\n",
    "Working hours are 9 AM to 5 PM. However, we allow flexible hours. \n",
    "Remote work is permitted on Fridays. \n",
    "NOTE: All expenses must be submitted by the 30th of each month. \n",
    "If you miss the deadline, you might not get paid back! 💸\n",
    "\"\"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "def clean_text(text):\n",
    "    # Remove emojis and special characters for cleaner processing\n",
    "    text = re.sub(r'[^\x00-\x7F]+', '', text) \n",
    "    # Remove extra whitespace\n",
    "    text = re.sub(r'\\s+', ' ', text).strip()\n",
    "    return text\n",
    "\n",
    "def chunk_text(text, chunk_size=2):\n",
    "    # Split text into sentences\n",
    "    sentences = sent_tokenize(text)\n",
    "    # Group sentences into chunks of 2 for better context\n",
    "    chunks = [\" \".join(sentences[i:i + chunk_size]) for i in range(0, len(sentences), chunk_size)]\n",
    "    return chunks\n",
    "\n",
    "# Processing\n",
    "cleaned_data = clean_text(raw_document)\n",
    "knowledge_chunks = chunk_text(cleaned_data)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Original Length: {len(raw_document)} chars\")\n",
    "print(f\"Number of Chunks created: {len(knowledge_chunks)}\")\n",
    "print(\"-\" * 30)\n",
    "for i, chunk in enumerate(knowledge_chunks):\n",
    "    print(f\"Chunk {i+1}: {chunk}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 🧠 Module 3: Simulating the \"Retrieval\" (RAG)\n",
    "NotebookLM doesn't read the whole library every time; it finds the most relevant page first. This is called **Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG)**."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def retrieve_relevant_chunk(query, chunks):\n",
    "    # Real-life logic: find which chunk contains the keywords from the query\n",
    "    query_words = query.lower().split()\n",
    "    best_chunk = None\n",
    "    max_matches = 0\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for chunk in chunks:\n",
    "        matches = sum(1 for word in query_words if word in chunk.lower())\n",
    "        if matches > max_matches:\n",
    "            max_matches = matches\n",
    "            best_chunk = chunk\n",
    "            \n",
    "    return best_chunk\n",
    "\n",
    "# TEST CASE 1: Asking about Vacation\n",
    "user_query_1 = \"How many vacation days do I get?\"\n",
    "context_1 = retrieve_relevant_chunk(user_query_1, knowledge_chunks)\n",
    "print(f\"Query: {user_query_1}\\nRetrieved Context: {context_1}\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# TEST CASE 2: Asking about Expenses\n",
    "user_query_2 = \"When should I submit my expenses?\"\n",
    "context_2 = retrieve_relevant_chunk(user_query_2, knowledge_chunks)\n",
    "print(f\"Query: {user_query_2}\\nRetrieved Context: {context_2}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 🤖 Module 4: The Final Prompt (The AI Interface)\n",
    "Now we combine the **User Question** + **Retrieved Context**. This prevents the AI from \"hallucinating\" (making things up)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def generate_grounded_prompt(query, context):\n",
    "    prompt = f\"\"\"\n",
    "    You are a helpful HR Assistant. Use ONLY the provided context to answer the question.\n",
    "    If the answer is not in the context, say \"I'm sorry, that information is not in the handbook.\"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    CONTEXT: \n",
    "    {context}\n",
    "    \n",
    "    QUESTION: \n",
    "    {query}\n",
    "    \n",
    "    ANSWER:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    return prompt\n",
    "\n",
    "# Testing the logic\n",
    "final_query = \"What is the policy for remote work?\"\n",
    "relevant_context = retrieve_relevant_chunk(final_query, knowledge_chunks)\n",
    "final_prompt = generate_grounded_prompt(final_query, relevant_context)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"--- FINAL PROMPT SENT TO AI ---\")\n",
    "print(final_prompt)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 🧪 Final Training Test: Edge Case Handling\n",
    "**Scenario:** Ask a question that is **NOT** in the document (e.g., \"What is the CEO's favorite color?\")."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "test_query = \"What is the CEO's favorite color?\"\n",
    "context = retrieve_relevant_chunk(test_query, knowledge_chunks)\n",
    "prompt = generate_grounded_prompt(test_query, context)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Query: {test_query}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Context Found: {context}\")\n",
    "print(\"\\nAI should respond based on the prompt instruction to say 'information not in handbook'.\")"
   ]
  }
